th of credit to all trial accounts, and you can use your credit to make sure it works in your country or target market. You can choose an SMS enabled Twilio number for a start. Be mindful of the fact that trial accounts have extra restrictions, for example, you may not have a local number available in your country for yourself (but you can send global SMS anyway), you will need to verify every number you send an SMS to beforehand and the message will be prefixed with a statement saying it\'s a Twilio trial account. Of course, these restrictions will be lifted when you have a paid subscription and do not apply to the excellent dev tools you can use to send SMS or access message history for debugging or testing.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Install <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-twilio-core/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WP Twilio Core</a>.</strong>\nWP Twilio core is a simple plugin to add SMS capability to your WordPress website using the Twilio API. It\'s available for free from WordPress.org. We have created this plugin so developers like us can extend it and integrate Twilio with a WordPress website of any niche/type. What it will allow you to do at this point is to send messages directly from your admin panel to any permissible (verified for trial accounts, remember?) number. The Event Espresso SMS Reminder plugin also depends on this plugin, so best to familiarise yourself with it before you make your purchase.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Read the <a href=\"https://www.twilio.com/help/faq/sms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twilio SMS FAQs</a>.</strong>\nThis is another important point, especially if the above steps aren\'t working for you. If you are already sending messages to your verified mobile numbers but somehow not having them delivered to you, then you may find your answer on Twilio\'s SMS FAQs. Make sure your target country/market and all their network providers are supported. They have pretty much made it clear who CANNOT receive a message. In India for instance, any number on the \"National Do Not Call Registry\" will not receive SMS via Twilio.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #1b1f2b;\">Requirements</span></h4>\nThere are a couple of requirements in order to use the Event Espresso SMS Reminder extension:\n<ol>\n 	<li>You must have a verified <a href=\"https://www.twilio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twilio</a> account (free trial or paid subscription).</li>\n 	<li>You must have the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-twilio-core/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WP Twilio Core WordPress plugin</a> (free) installed (1.2.0+).</li>\n 	<li>You must be using Contact form 7 plugin on your website .</li>\n</ol>\";s:17:\"short_description\";s:110:\"\nUsing Contact Form 7 SMS plugin ,You will receive SMS notification when someone fills the forms and hit send.\";s:10:\"banner_url\";s:61:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6687/banner.png\";s:15:\"card_banner_url\";s:66:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6687/card_banner.png\";s:15:\"selling_point_0\";s:36:\"Increase your web site\'s engagement.\";s:15:\"selling_point_1\";s:63:\"Satisfy your customers showing them that you are on their back.\";s:15:\"selling_point_2\";s:54:\"Provide a Top-notch reminder and notification service.\";s:11:\"screenshots\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"1758\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2020-08-03 16:45:18\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2020-08-03 10:22:55\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;}s:10:\"is_premium\";b:0;s:14:\"premium_suffix\";s:9:\"(Premium)\";s:7:\"is_live\";b:1;s:10:\"public_key\";s:32:\"pk_31f62eea25b0e626eefc7e0c79d35\";s:10:\"secret_key\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"6687\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2020-11-23 23:55:02\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2020-08-03 10:01:34\";s:22:\"\0FS_Entity\0_is_updated\";b:0;s:22:\"premium_releases_count\";i:4;s:9:\"bundle_id\";N;s:17:\"bundle_public_key\";N;}i:8;O:9:\"FS_Plugin\":23:{s:16:\"parent_plugin_id\";s:4:\"2894\";s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Woocommerce Bookings\";s:4:\"slug\";s:6:\"wcbkng\";s:12:\"premium_slug\";s:14:\"wcbkng-premium\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"plugin\";s:20:\"affiliate_moderation\";N;s:19:\"is_wp_org_compliant\";b:0;s:4:\"file\";N;s:7:\"version\";N;s:11:\"auto_update\";N;s:4:\"info\";O:14:\"FS_Plugin_Info\":13:{s:9:\"plugin_id\";s:4:\"6780\";s:11:\"description\";s:5142:\"The Woocommerce SMS for Twilio plugin will allow you to send SMS Your customers on your store powered by the Woocommerce and WooCommerce Bookings plugins. The plugin integrates the SMS service from <a href=\"https://www.twilio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twilio</a>, which is reasonably priced with an excellent API, via our <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-twilio-core/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WP Twilio Core</a> plugin on the WordPress.org repository.\n\nAfter activating the plugin, all you have to do is select the registration question for mobile number to send SMS to your customers when they apply any action on the store. (Make a purchase,\n\n&nbsp;\n<h4><span style=\"color: #1b1f2b;\">Woocommerce SMS Features</span></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Send notifications by SMS as per the bookings statuses.</li>\n 	<li>Send SMS notifications to the admin (Shop manager) or any number you want, full reports about the new orders or order statuses</li>\n 	<li>Customize the SMS message for the admin</li>\n 	<li>Customize the sms for each status (Pending,On hold,Completed,Confirmed, Shipped,Failed,Cancelled,Refunded)</li>\n 	<li>Customer profile details shortcodes to customize the sms (<strong>%shop_name%, %resource_id%,%resource_type%,%order_id%, %order_count%, %order_amount%, %order_status%, %billing_name%, %shipping_name%, %shipping_method%</strong>. )</li>\n 	<li>Opt-in Checkbox Label and Opt-in Checkbox Option</li>\n 	<li>Leverage the excellent Twilio API via our WP Twilio Core plugin</li>\n</ul>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #1b1f2b;\">WP Twilio Core Features</span></h4>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Optionally shorten URLs using Bit.ly or Google URL Shortener API</li>\n 	<li>Basic logging capability to keep track of up to 100 entries</li>\n 	<li>Directly send a text message to any permissible number from the admin panel for testing</li>\n</ul>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #1b1f2b;\">Pre-Purchase Checklist</span></h4>\nSince Twilio API is a paid service, we suggest you make sure it will work for you before you purchase the plugin. Here\'s how to do it:\n<ol>\n 	<li><strong>Sign up for Twilio\'s <a href=\"https://www.twilio.com/help/faq/twilio-basics/how-does-twilios-free-trial-work\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Free Trial</a>.</strong>\nYes you can! They give a few dollars worth of credit to all trial accounts, and you can use your credit to make sure it works in your country or target market. You can choose an SMS enabled Twilio number for a start. Be mindful of the fact that trial accounts have extra restrictions, for example, you may not have a local number available in your country for yourself (but you can send global SMS anyway), you will need to verify every number you send an SMS to beforehand and the message will be prefixed with a statement saying it\'s a Twilio trial account. Of course, these restrictions will be lifted when you have a paid subscription and do not apply to the excellent dev tools you can use to send SMS or access message history for debugging or testing.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Install <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-twilio-core/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WP Twilio Core</a>.</strong>\nWP Twilio core is a simple plugin to add SMS capability to your WordPress website using the Twilio API. It\'s available for free from WordPress.org. We have created this plugin so developers like us can extend it and integrate Twilio with a WordPress website of any niche/type. What it will allow you to do at this point is to send messages directly from your admin panel to any permissible (verified for trial accounts, remember?) number. The Event Espresso SMS Reminder plugin also depends on this plugin, so best to familiarise yourself with it before you make your purchase.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Read the <a href=\"https://www.twilio.com/help/faq/sms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twilio SMS FAQs</a>.</strong>\nThis is another important point, especially if the above steps aren\'t working for you. If you are already sending messages to your verified mobile numbers but somehow not having them delivered to you, then you may find your answer on Twilio\'s SMS FAQs. Make sure your target country/market and all their network providers are supported. They have pretty much made it clear who CANNOT receive a message. In India for instance, any number on the \"National Do Not Call Registry\" will not receive SMS via Twilio.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #1b1f2b;\">Requirements</span></h4>\nThere are a couple of requirements in order to use the WooCommerce Bookings extension:\n<ol>\n 	<li>You must have a verified <a href=\"https://www.twilio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twilio</a> account (free trial or paid subscription).</li>\n 	<li>You must have the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-twilio-core/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WP Twilio Core WordPress plugin</a> (free) installed (1.2.0+).</li>\n 	<li>You must be using woocommerce on your website .</li>\n 	<li>You must have created a Mobile Number question (text field) and made sure it appears on the registration forms.</li>\n</ol>\";s:17:\"short_description\";s:123:\"\nThe WPSMS for WooCommerce Bookings plugin will allow you to send SMS to your customers to notify them about their bookings\";s:10:\"banner_url\";s:61:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6780/banner.png\";s:15:\"card_banner_url\";s:66:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6780/card_banner.png\";s:15:\"selling_point_